# Debugging & triage

## Triage first

- Reproduce the failure reliably, characterize the symptom, and scope the blast
  radius before forming hypotheses. A bug you can't reproduce, you can't confirm fixed.

## Method

- Test one hypothesis/variable at a time — unless deliberately running a
  `git bisect`-style search.
- Form a hypothesis → change one thing → observe → repeat. Don't shotgun several
  fixes at once and lose track of which one mattered.

## Running checks

- Linters/validators → `my-linting`. Tests → `my-testing`. Editor (Neovim) ops → `my-editor-neovim`.
